          From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia                            Jump to:     navigation,      search           Hajduk Split  1952 season   Chairman Marin Vidan   Manager Jozo Matošić   First League 1st   Top goalscorer Bernard Vukas (9)      ← 1951 1952–53 →      The 1952 season was the 41st season in Hajduk Split’s history and their 6th in the Yugoslav First League. Their 3rd place finish in the 1951 season meant it was their 6th successive season playing in the Yugoslav First League.    Contents   1 Competitions  1.1 Overall 1.2 Yugoslav First League  1.2.1 Classification 1.2.2 Preliminary stage (group 2) 1.2.3 Final Round (championship group) 1.2.4 Results summary 1.2.5 Results by round     2 Matches  2.1 Yugoslav First League   3 Player seasonal records  3.1 Top scorers   4 See also 5 External sources    Competitions[edit] Overall[edit]   Competition Started round Final result First match Last Match   1952 Yugoslav First League – 1st 2 March 22 June   Yugoslav First League[edit] Classification[edit] Preliminary stage (group 2)[edit]   Pos Team Pld W D L GF GA GD Pts Qualification or relegation   1 Red Star !Red Star 10 7 0 3 20 16 +4 14 0 Championship group0   2 Hajduk Split !Hajduk Split 10 6 0 4 23 11 +12 12   3 BSK Belgrade !BSK Belgrade 10 4 2 4 19 12 +7 10 0 Central group0   4 Vardar !Vardar 10 5 0 5 13 18 −5 10   5 NK Zagreb !NK Zagreb 10 3 2 5 7 12 −5 8 0 Relegation group0   6 Sarajevo !Sarajevo 10 3 0 7 8 21 −13 6   Source: rsssf.com Rules for classification: 1) points; 2) goal difference; 3) number of goals scored (C) = Champion; (R) = Relegated; (P) = Promoted; (E) = Eliminated; (O) = Play-off winner; (A) = Advances to a further round. Only applicable when the season is not finished: (Q) = Qualified to the phase of tournament indicated; (TQ) = Qualified to tournament, but not yet to the particular phase indicated; (RQ) = Qualified to the relegation tournament indicated; (DQ) = Disqualified from tournament. Final Round (championship group)[ed